Comment: My favorite first move. King's pawn defense.
He replies, mirroring my first move.
I threaten his pawn and develop my knight.
He protects with his knight.
I attack his e-pawn, being protected by my queen and my knight.
He takes my pawn with his own.
I take with the knight.
I thought he would just take the knight, but he decides to put pressure on it instead.
I just simply take the knight.
He takes back, now with doubled up pawns and an open king.
Developing.
My opponent looking to castle queenside.
Now, if he castles queenside, I will pin his queen to his rook.
He falls for the trap, and castles queenside.
I pin his queen to his rook with my bishop.
Moves out of the way.
I take his rook.
He takes my bishop and now I am +2 and in a good position.
Wanting to develop my bishop, I protect the g2 square.
He develops his knight.
